The paper deals with timing analysis in hierarchical design flow, which is a topic related to electronic design automation (EDA) and circuit design. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.ET (Emerging Technologies), which covers research on EDA and related topics. The paper also proposes methods for extracting timing models and reconstructing correlation between modules, which are related to circuit modeling and simulation. This makes cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) and cs.DC (Digital Circuits) likely categories as well. The paper also mentions statistical timing analysis, which is a technique used to evaluate the performance of digital circuits. This makes cs.EM (Electromagnetics) and cs.SY (Systems and Control) possible categories, as they cover research on circuit simulation and control systems, respectively.
